Information: ABT-263 (Navitoclax) is a potent inhibitor of Bcl-xL; Bcl-2 and Bcl-w with Ki of <= 0.5 nM; <=1 nM and <=1 nM; but binds more weakly to Mcl-1 and A1. Phase 1/2.
Clofarabine inhibits the enzymatic activities of ribonucleotide reductase (IC50 = 65 nM) and DNA polymerase.

BEZ235 (NVP-BEZ235) is a dual ATP-competitive PI3K and mTOR inhibitor for p110A/gamma/δ/Beta and mTOR(p70S6K) with IC50 of 4 nM/5 nM/7 nM/75 nM/6 nM; respectively. Inhibits ATR with IC50 of 21 nM; shown to be poor inhibitory to Akt and PDK1. Phase 1/2.
KU-0063794 is a potent and highly specific dual-mTOR inhibitor of mTORC1 and mTORC2 with IC50 of ~10 nM; no effect on PI3Ks.
CI-1040 (PD 184352) is an ATP non-competitive MEK1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 17 nM; 100-fold more selective for MEK1/2 than MEK5. Phase 2.
Temozolomide is a DNA damage inducer.

Motesanib Diphosphate (AMG-706) is a potent ATP-competitive inhibitor of VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 2 nM/3 nM/6 nM; respectively; similar activity against Kit; ~10-fold more selective for VEGFR than PDGFR and Ret. Phase 1/2.
Dienogest is an orally active synthetic progesterone (or progestin).
STF-62247 shows selectivtoxicity and growth inhibition of renal cells lacking VHL; 25-fold greater sensitivity observed for cells with VHL deficiency compared to wild-type (VHL+).
Celecoxib is a selective COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 40 nM.
Y-27632 2HCl is a selective ROCK1 (p160ROCK) inhibitor with Ki of 140 nM; exhibits >200-fold selectivity over other kinases; including PKC; cAMP-dependent protein kinase; MLCK and PAK.
Adapalene is a third-generation topical retinoid primarily used in the treatment of acne.
Masitinib is a novel inhibitor for Kit and PDGFRA/Beta with IC50 of 200 nM and 540 nM/800 nM; weak inhibition to ABL and c-Fms. Phase 2/3.
Budesonide is a glucocorticoid steroid for the treatment of asthma; non-infectious rhinitis.
ZSTK474 inhibits class I PI3Kisoforms with IC50 of 37 nM; mostly PI3Kδ.
Floxuridine is a prodrugs of floxuridine and an oncology agent with an GI50 of 5.1 muM for the inhibition of MDCK/PEPT1.
Belinostat (PXD101) is a novel HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 27 nM; with activity demonstrated in cisplatin-resistant tumors. Phase 1/2.
Costunolide; a natural sesquiterpene compound with multiple biological activities; inhibits FPTase with IC50 of 20 muM; also inhibits telomerase with IC50 of 65-90 muM.
LAQ824 (Dacinostat) is a novel HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 32 nM and is known to activate the p21 promoter.
Flumazenil is a benzodiazepine antagonist.
GDC-0879 is a novel; potent; and selective B-Raf inhibitor with IC50 of 0.13 nM with activity against c-Raf as well; no inhibition known to other protein kinases.
Granisetron HCl is a serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist
4mu8C is a potent and selective IRE1 RNase inhibitor with IC50 of 76 nM.
RG2833 (RGFP109) is a brain-penetrant HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 60 nM and 50 nM for HDAC1 and HDAC3; respectively.
SGX-523 is a selective Met inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM; no activity to BRAFV599E; c-Raf; Abl and p38A. Phase 1.
Losartan is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist; competes with the binding of angiotensin II to AT1 receptors with IC50 of 20 nM.
Everolimus (RAD001) is an mTOR inhibitor of FKBP12 with IC50 of 1.6-2.4 nM.
Acitretin is a second generation retinoid used for psoriasis.
AT9283 is a potent JAK2/3 inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM/1.1 nM; also potent to Aurora A/B; Abl(T315I). Phase 1/2.
Lopinavir is a potent HIV protease inhibitor with Ki of 1.3 pM.
Ivacaftor (VX-770) is a potentiator of CFTR targeting G551D-CFTR and F508del-CFTR with EC50 of 100 nM and 25 nM; respectively.
Ondansetron HCl is a serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist.
S3I-201 shows potent inhibition of STAT3 DNA-binding activity with IC50 of 86 muM; and low activity towards STAT1 and STAT5.
Tenofovir disoproxil fumarate belongs to nucleotide analogue reverse transcriptase inhibitors (nRTIs).

ABT-751 (E7010) binds to the colchicine site on Beta-tubulin and inhibits polymerization of microtubules; not a substrate for the MDR transporter and is active against cell lines resistant to vincristine; doxorubicin; and cisplatin. Phase 1/2.
Clopidogrel (Plavix) is an oral; thienopyridine class antiplatelet agent.
WZ4002 is a novel; mutant-selective EGFR inhibitor for EGFR(L858R)/(T790M) with IC50 of 2 nM/8 nM; does not inhibit ERBB2 phosphorylation (T798I).
Tianeptine is a selective serotonin reuptake enhancer (SSRE) compound used for treating major depressive episodes.

Danoprevir (ITMN-191) is a peptidomimetic inhibitor of the NS3/4A protease of hepatitis C virus (HCV) with IC50 of 0.2-3.5 nM; inhibition effect for HCV genotypes 1A/1B/4/5/6 is ~10-fold higher than 2B/3A. Phase 2.
Ziprasidone HCl was the fifth atypical antipsychotic.

Thalidomide was introduced as a sedative drug; immunomodulatory agent and also is investigated for treating symptoms of many cancers. Thalidomide inhibits an E3 ubiquitin ligase; which is a CRBN-DDB1-Cul4A complex.Phase 3.
Cilomilast is a potent PDE4 inhibitor with IC50 of about 110 nM; has anti-inflammatory activity and low central nervous system activity.
Dimesna is an uroprotective agent used to decrease urotoxicity.
Moxifloxacin is a fourth-generation synthetic fluoroquinolone antibacterial agent.
Methotrexate is an antimetabolite and antifolate drug; which acts by inhibiting the metabolism of folic acid.
AS-703026 is a highly selective; potent; ATP non-competitive allosteric inhibitor of MEK1/2 with IC50 of 5 nM-2 muM in MM cell lines. Phase 1/2.
JIB-04 is a pan-selective Jumonji histone demethylase inihibitor with IC50 of 230; 340; 855; 445; 435; 1100; and 290 nM for JARID1A; JMJD2E; JMJD3; JMJD2A; JMJD2B; JMJD2C; and JMJD2D; respectively.
STF-118804 is a highly specific NAMPT inhibitor.
ABT-737 is a BH3 mimetic inhibitor of Bcl-xL; Bcl-2 and Bcl-w with EC50 of 78.7 nM; 30.3 nM and 197.8 nM; respectively; no inhibition observed against Mcl-1; Bcl-B or Bfl-1. Phase 2.
YM201636 is a selective PIKfyve inhibitor with IC50 of 33 nM; less potent to p110A and insensitive to Fabl (yeast orthologue).
Nintedanib (BIBF 1120) is a potent triple angiokinase inhibitor for VEGFR1/2/3; FGFR1/2/3 and PDGFRA/Beta with IC50 of 34 nM/13 nM/13 nM; 69 nM/37 nM/108 nM and 59 nM/65 nM. Phase 3.
Raloxifene is estrogen antagonists; inhibits human cytosolic aldehyde oxidase-catalyzed phthalazine oxidation activity with IC50 of 5.7 nM.
Dasatinib is a novel; potent and multi-targeted inhibitor that targets Abl; Src and c-Kit; with IC50 of ＜1 nM; 0.8 nM and 79 nM; respectively.
Vincristine is an inhibitor of polymerization of microtubules by binding to tubulin with IC50 of 32 muM.
Nilotinib (AMN-107) is a Bcr-Abl inhibitor with IC50 less than 30 nM.
Entecavir hydrate belongs to the family of medicines called antivirals.
Sunitinib Malate is a multi-targeted RTK inhibitor targeting VEGFR2 (Flk-1) and PDGFRBeta with IC50 of 80 nM and 2 nM; and also inhibits c-Kit.

Avagacestat (BMS-708163) is a potent; selective; orally bioavailable gamma-secretase inhibitor of ABeta40 and ABeta42 with IC50 of 0.3 nM and 0.27 nM; demonstrating a 193-fold selectivity against Notch. Phase 2.
Elesclomol (STA-4783) is a novel potent oxidative stress inducer that elicits pro-apoptosis events among tumor cells.
Altretamine is an anti-neoplastic agent.
GDC-0941 is a potent inhibitor of PI3KA/δ with IC50 of 3 nM; with modest selectivity against p110Beta (11-fold) and p110gamma (25-fold).
Bumetanide (Bumex) is a loop diuretic of the sulfamyl category to treat heart failure.
SB216763 is a potent and selective GSK-3 inhibitor with IC50 of 34.3 nM for GSK-3A and equally effective at inhibiting human GSK-3Beta.
FT-207 (NSC 148958) is a substance being used in the treatment of some types of cancer.
BSI-201 (Iniparib; SAR240550) is a PARP1 inhibitor with demonstrated effectiveness in triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC). Phase 3.
Dexamethasone is an anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressant.

JNJ-26481585 is a novel second-generation HDAC inhibitor with highest potency for HDAC1 with IC50 of 0.11 nM; modest potent to HDACs 2; 4; 10; and 11; greater than 30-fold selectivity against HDACs 3; 5; 8; and 9 and lowest potency to HDACs 6 and 7. Phase 2.
Fluoxetine HCl is an antidepressant of the selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) class.

LY294002 is the first synthetic molecule known to inhibit PI3KA/δ/Beta with IC50 of 0.5 muM/0.57 muM/0.97 muM; respectively; more stable in solution than Wortmannin; and also blocks autophagosome formation.
Ivermectin is a broad-spectrum antiparasitic medication.
SGI-1027 is a DNMT inhibitor with IC50 of 6; 8; 7.5 muM for DNMT1; DNMT3A; and DNMT3B
ZCL278 is a selective Cdc42 GTPase inhibitor with Kd of 11.4 muM.
GSK690693 is a pan-Akt inhibitor targeting Akt1/2/3 with IC50 of 2 nM/13 nM/9 nM; also sensitive to the AGC kinase family: PKA; PrkX and PKC isozymes. Phase 1.
GSK1059615 is a dual inhibitor of PI3KA/Beta/δ/gamma (reversible) and mTOR with IC50 of 0.4 nM/0.6 nM/2 nM/5 nM and 12 nM; respectively. Phase 1.
TW-37 is a novel nonpeptide inhibitor to recombinant Bcl-2; Bcl-xL and Mcl-1 with Ki of 0.29 muM; 1.11 muM and 0.26 muM; respectively.
Cefoselis sulfate is an antibiotic.
Malotilate is a liver protein metabolism improved compound.
Meropenem is an ultra-broad spectrum injectable antibiotic.

SNS-032 has firstly been described as a selective inhibitor of CDK2 with IC50 of 48 nM and is 10- and 20-fold selective over CDK1/CDK4. It is also found to be sensitive to CDK7/9 with IC50 of 62 nM/4 nM; with little effect on CDK6. Phase 1.
Oxcarbazepine inhibits the binding of [3H]BTX to sodium channels with IC50 of 160 muM and also inhibits the influx of 22Na+ into rat brain synaptosomes with IC50 about 100 muM.
Capecitabine is a tumor-selective fluoropyrimidine carbamate which achieves higher intratumoral 5-FU level with lower toxicity than 5-FU.
Tenofovir blocks reverse transcriptase and hepatitis B virus infections.
Cisplatin is an inorganic platinum complex; which is able to inhibit DNA synthesis by forming DNA adducts.

Droxinostat (CMH; 5809354) is a selective inhibitor of HDAC; mostly for HDACs 6 and 8 with IC50 of 2.47muM and 1.46 muM; greater than 8-fold selective against HDAC3 and no inhibition to HDAC1; 2; 4; 5; 7; 9; and 10.
MK-2866 (GTx-024) is a selective androgen receptor modulator (SARM) with Ki of 3.8 nM; and is tissue-selective for anabolic organs. Phase 3.
Tizanidine HCl is an A2-adrenergic receptor agonist and inhibits neurotransmitter release from CNS noradrenergic neurons.
Ritonavir is an antiretroviral drug which inhibits a particular liver enzyme that normally metabolizes protease inhibitors; cytochrome P450-3A4 (CYP3A4).
Zonisamide is a sulfonamide anticonvulsant approved for use as an adjunctive.
CUDC-101 is a potent multi-targeted inhibitor against HDAC; EGFR and HER2 with IC50 of 4.4 nM; 2.4 nM; and 15.7 nM; and inhibits class I/II HDACs; but not class III; Sir-type HDACs. Phase 1.
Zibotentan (ZD4054) is a specific Endothelin (ETA) antagonist with IC50 of 21 nM; exhibiting no activity at ETB. Phase 3.
Dutasteride is a dual 5-A reductase inhibitor that inhibits conversion of testosterone to dihydrotestosterone (DHT).
Calcitriol is the hormonally active form of vitamin D.
Imiquimod is a novel synthetic agent with immune response modifying activity.
SB525334 is a potent and selective inhibitor of TGFBeta receptor I (ALK5) with IC50 of 14.3 nM; is 4-fold less potent to ALK4 than ALK5 and inactive to ALK2; 3; and 6.
CO-1686 is an irreversible; mutant-selective EGFR inhibitor with Ki of 21.5 nM and 303.3 nM for EGFRL858R/T790M and EGFRWT; respectively. Phase 1/2.
WZ4003 is a highly specific NUAK kinase inhibitor with IC50 of 20 nM and 100 nM for NUAK1 and NUAK2; respectively; without significant inhibition on 139 other kinases.

Linifanib (ABT-869) is a novel; potent ATP-competitive VEGFR/PDGFR inhibitor for KDR; CSF-1R; Flt-1/3 and PDGFRBeta with IC50 of 4 nM; 3 nM; 3 nM/4 nM and 66 nM respectively; mostly effective in mutant kinase-dependent cancer cells (i.e. FLT3). Phase 3.

OSI-930 is a potent inhibitor of Kit; KDR and CSF-1R with IC50 of 80 nM; 9 nM and 15 nM; respectively; also potent to Flt-1; c-Raf and Lck and low activity against PDGFRA/Beta; Flt-3 and Abl. Phase 1.

Afatinib (BIBW2992) irreversibly inhibits EGFR/HER2 including EGFR(wt); EGFR(L858R); EGFR(L858R/T790M) and HER2 with IC50 of 0.5 nM; 0.4 nM; 10 nM and 14 nM; respectively; 100-fold more active against Gefitinib-resistant L858R-T790M EGFR mutant. Phase 3.
Idarubicin HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of Idarubicin which is an anthracycline antibiotic and a DNA topoisomerase II (topo II) inhibitor for MCF-7 cells with IC50 of 3.3 ng/mL.
Ridaforolimus (Deforolimus) is a selective mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 nM; while not classified as a prodrug; mTOR inhibition and FKBP12 binding is similar to rapamycin.
Agomelatine is classified as a norepinephrine-dopamine disinhibitor (NDDI) due to its antagonism of the 5-HT2C receptor.
NVP-AEW541 is a potent inhibitor of IGF-1R with IC50 of 86 nM; 27-fold greater selectivity for IGF-1R than InsR.
Nepafenac is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agent.

Tandutinib (MLN518; CT53518) is a potent FLT3 antagonist with IC50 of 0.22 muM; also inhibits PDGFR and c-Kit; 15 to 20-fold higher potency for FLT3 versus CSF-1R and >100-fold selectivity for the same target versus FGFR; EGFR and KDR. Phase 1/2.
PD173074 is a potent FGFR1 inhibitor with IC50 of ~25 nM and also inhibits VEGFR2 with IC50 of 100-200 nM; ~1000-fold selective for FGFR1 than PDGFR and c-Src.
Entinostat (MS-275) strongly inhibits HDAC1 and HDAC3 with IC50 of 0.51 muM and 1.7 muM; compared with HDACs 4; 6; 8; and 10. Phase 1/2.
Amisulpride is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat psychosis in schizophrenia and episodes of mania in bipolar disorder.
SL327 is a selective inhibitor for MEK1/2 with IC50 of 0.18 muM/ 0.22 muM; no activity towards Erk1; MKK3; MKK4; c-JUN; PKC; PKA; or CamKII;capable of transport through the blood-brain barrier.
Camptothecin is a specific inhibitor of DNA topoisomerase I (Topo I) with IC50 of 0.68 muM. Phase 2.
SB203580 is a p38 MAPK inhibitor with IC50 of 0.3-0.5 muM; 10-fold less sensitive to SAPK3(106T) and SAPK4(106T) and blocks PKB phosphorylation with IC50 of 3-5 muM.
Ifosfamide is a nitrogen mustard alkylating agent used in the treatment of cancer.
NVP-ADW742 is an IGF-1R inhibitor with IC50 of 0.17 muM; >16-fold more potent against IGF-1R than InsR;  little activity to HER2; PDGFR; VEGFR-2; Bcr-Abl and c-Kit.
Doxazosin mesylate is an alpha-1 adrenergic receptor blocker.
BTZ043 racemate is a decaprenylphosphoryl-Beta-D-ribose 2'-epimerase (DprE1) inhibitor acting as a new antimycobacterial agent that kill Mycobacterium tuberculosis.

Flupirtine maleate is the salt form of Flupirtine; which is a centrally acting non-opioid analgesia; is a selective neuronal potassium channel opener that also has NMDA receptor antagonist properties. Phase 2.
OSU-03012 is a potent inhibitor of recombinant PDK-1 with IC50 of 5 muM and 2-fold increase in potency over OSU-02067.
TG100115 is a PI3Kgamma/δ inhibitor with IC50 of 83 nM/235 nM; with little effect on PI3KA/Beta. Phase 1/2.
Suvorexant (MK-4305) is a potent dual OX receptor antagonist with Ki of 0.55 nM and 0.35 nM for OX1 receptor and OX2 receptor; respectively. Phase 3.
IWP-L6 is a highly potent Porcn inhibitor with EC50 of 0.5 nM.
JNJ-38877605 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-Met with IC50 of 4 nM; 600-fold selective for c-Met than 200 other tyrosine and serine-threonine kinases. Phase 1.
MGCD-265 is a potent; multi-target and ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-Met and VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 1 nM; 3 nM/3 nM/4 nM; respectively; also inhibits Ron and Tie2. Phase 1/2.

Mocetinostat (MGCD0103) is a potent HDAC inhibitor with most potency for HDAC1 with IC50 of 0.15 muM; 2- to 10- fold selectivity against HDAC2; 3; and 11; and no activity to HDAC4; 5; 6; 7; and 8. Phase 1/2.
Daptomycin is a novel antibiotic with rapid in vitro bactericidal activity against gram-positive organisms.
Brivanib alaninate (BMS-582664) is the prodrug of BMS-540215; an ATP-competitive inhibitor against VEGFR2 with IC50 of 25 nM.
Mianserin HCl is a psychoactive agent of the tetracyclic antidepressant.
AZD1152-HQPA (Barasertib) is a highly selective Aurora B inhibitor with IC50 of 0.37 nM; ~100 fold more selective for Aurora B over Aurora A.
Pelitinib (EKB-569) is a potent irreversible EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 38.5 nM. Phase2.

CEP-18770 is an orally active inhibitor of the chymotrypsin-like activity of proteasome with IC50 of 3.8 nM; with only marginal inhibition of the tryptic and peptidylglutamyl activities of the proteosome. Phase 1/2.

Tigecycline is bacteriostatic and is a protein synthesis inhibitor by binding to the 30S ribosomal subunit of bacteria and thereby blocking entry of Aminoacyl-tRNA into the A site of the ribosome during prokaryotic translation.
CP-724;714 is a potent; selective inhibitor of HER2/ErbB2 with IC50 of 10 nM; >640-fold selectivity against EGFR; InsR; IRG-1R; PDGFR; VEGFR2; Abl; Src; c-Met etc. Phase 2.
Prazosin hydrochloride; a quinazoline derivative; is the first of a new chemical class of antihypertensives.
BIIB021 is an orally available; fully synthetic small-molecule inhibitor of HSP90 with Ki and EC50 of 1.7 nM and 38 nM; respectively.
Topiramate is an anticonvulsant compound.
BIBR 1532 is a potent; selective; non-competitive telomerase inhibitor with IC50 of 100 nM.
Elaiophylin shows antiprotozoal activity against Plasmodium falciparum K1a and Trypanosoma brucei brucei GUTat 3.1 strains with IC50 of 0.36 muM and 0.45 muM; respectively.
TAK-700 (Orteronel) is a potent and highly selective human 17;20-lyase inhibitor with IC50 of 38 nM; exhibits >1000-fold selectivity over other CYPs (e.g. 11-hydroxylase and CYP3A4). Phase 3.
Atazanavir is a HIV protease inhibitor with Ki of 2.66 nM.
Melatonin is a hormone produced in the brain by the pineal gland from the amino acid tryptophan.
Doxercalciferol is a synthetic analog of vitamin D.
Bendamustine HCL is a DNA-damaging agent with IC50 of 50 muM.
Oligomycin A is an inhibitor of ATP synthase; inhibits oxidative phosphorylation and all the ATP-dependent processes occurring on the coupling membrane of mitochondria.
NMS-873 is an allosteric and specific p97 inhibitor with IC50 of 30 nM.
EHop-016 is a specific Rac GTPase inhibitor with IC50 of 1.1 muM for Rac1; equally potent inhibition for Rac3.
Veliparib (ABT-888) is a potent inhibitor of PARP1 and PARP2 with Ki of 5.2 nM and 2.9 nM; respectively. It is inactive to SIRT2. Phase 1/2.
Dacarbazine is an antineoplastic chemotherapy drug used in the treatment of various cancers.
Bortezomib (PS-341) is a potent 20S proteasome inhibitor with Ki of 0.6 nM.
Fludarabine Phosphate is an analogue of adenosine and deoxyadenosine; which is able to compete with dATP for incorporation into DNA and inhibit DNA synthesis.
Erlotinib HCl (OSI-744) is an EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 2 nM; >1000-fold more sensitive for EGFR than human c-Src or v-Abl. Phase 3.
Amuvatinib (MP-470) is a potent and multi-targeted inhibitor of c-Kit; PDGFRA and Flt3 with IC50 of 10 nM; 40 nM and 81 nM; respectively. Phase 2.
Pazopanib (GW786034) is a novel multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1; VEGFR2; VEGFR3; PDGFR; FGFR; c-Kit and c-Fms with IC50 of 10 nM; 30 nM; 47 nM; 84 nM; 74 nM; 140 nM and 146 nM; respectively.
Rufinamide; a triazole derivative; is an anticonvulsant medication.
Temsirolimus (CCI-779) is a specific mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 1.76 muM.

WYE-354 is a potent; specific and ATP-competitive inhibitor of mTOR with IC50 of 5 nM; blocks mTORC1/P-S6K(T389) and mTORC2/P-AKT(S473) not P-AKT(T308); selective for mTOR than PI3KA (>100-fold) and PI3Kgamma (>500-fold).
Enzastaurin (LY317615) is a potent PKCBeta selective inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM; 6- to 20-fold selectivity against PKCA; PKCgamma and PKCE. Phase 3.
Aniracetam is a nootropics and neuroprotective drug.
SB431542 is a potent and selective inhibitor of ALK5 with IC50 of 94 nM; 100-fold more selective for ALK5 than p38 MAPK and other kinases.
Carmofur is a pyrimidine analogue used as an antineoplastic agent.
SB202190 (FHPI) is a potent p38 MAPK inhibitor targeting p38A/Beta with IC50 of 50 nM/100 nM; sometimes used instead of SB 203580 to investigate potential roles for SAPK2a/p38 in vivo.
Megestrol Acetate is a synthetic progesteronal agent with an IC50 of 260 muM for the inhibition of HegG2.
PCI-24781 is a novel pan-HDAC inhibitor mostly targeting HDAC1 with Ki of 7 nM; modest potent to HDACs 2; 3; 6; and 10 and greater than 40-fold selectivity against HDAC8. Phase 1/2.
Edaravone; a strong novel free radical scavenger; is used for treatment of patients with acute brain infarction.
Rucaparib (AG-014699; PF-01367338) is an inhibitor of PARP with Ki of 1.4 nM for PARP1; also showing binding affinity to eight other PARP domains. Phase 1/2.
Fluvoxamine maleate is a selective serotonin (5-HT) reuptake inhibitor (SSRI).

Danusertib (PHA-739358) is an Aurora kinase inhibitor for Aurora A/B/C with IC50 of 13 nM/79 nM/61 nM; modestly potent to Abl; TrkA; c-RET and FGFR1; and less potent to Lck; VEGFR2/3; c-Kit; CDK2; etc. Phase 2.
Ketoconazole inhibits cyclosporine oxidase and testosterone 6 beta-hydroxylase with IC50 of 0.19 mM and 0.22 mM; respectively.
Edoxaban is a selective factor Xa inhibitor with Ki of 0.561 nM; >10 000-fold selectivity over thrombin and FIXa; and is also an orally bioavailable anticoagulant drug.
Rilpivirine is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI); and used to treat HIV-1 infection.

Odanacatib (MK 0822) is a potent; selective; and neutral inhibitor of cathepsin K (human/rabbit) with IC50 of 0.2 nM/1 nM; and demonstrated high selectivity versus off-target cathepsin B; L; S. Phase 3.
Rigosertib (ON-01910) is a non-ATP-competitive inhibitor of PLK1 with IC50 of 9 nM. It shows 30-fold greater selectivity against Plk2 and no activity to Plk3. Phase 3.

BMS-754807 is a potent and reversible inhibitor of IGF-1R/InsR with IC50 of 1.8 nM/1.7 nM; less potent to Met; Aurora A/B; TrkA/B and Ron; and shows little activity to Flt3; Lck; MK2; PKA; PKC etc. Phase 1/2.
Doripenem Hydrate is an ultra-broad spectrum injectable antibiotic.
ADL5859 HCl is a δ-opioid receptor agonist with Ki of 0.8 nM; selectivity against opioid receptor k; mu; and weak inhibitory activity at the hERG channel. Phase 2.
Mizoribine is an imidazole nucleoside; selectively inhibits inosine monophosphate synthetase and guanosine monophosphate synthetase.
Docetaxel; an analog of taxol; is an inhibitor of depolymerisation of microtubules by binding to stabilized microtubules.
Pirarubicin is an anthracycline agent.

MK-8245 is an liver-targeting inhibitor of stearoyl-CoA desaturase (SCD) with IC50 of 1 nM for human SCD1 and 3 nM for both rat SCD1 and mouse SCD1; with anti-diabetic and anti-dyslipidemic efficacy. Phase 2.
Trilostane is an inhibitor of 3 Beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase used in the treatment of Cushing’s syndrome.
Valproic acid sodium salt (Sodium valproate) is a HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 0.4 mM and also inhibits GABA-transaminase or succinic semialdehyde dehydrogenase.
Ranolazine 2HCl; is an antianginal medication.
PD98059 is a non-ATP competitive MEK inhibitor with IC50 of 2 muM; specifically inhibits MEK-1-mediated activation of MAPK; does not directly inhibit ERK1 or ERK2.
Tranilast is an antiallergic compound.
Anastrozole is a third-generation nonsteroidal selective aromatase inhibitor.

Nanchangmycin (dianemycin) is a polyether antibiotic with similar structure to dianemycin and is very active against a broad spectrum of harmful nematodes and insects but not for for mammals and plants.
Exemestane is an aromatase inhibitor; inhibits human placental and rat ovarian aromatase with IC50 of 30 nM and 40 nM; respectively.
VX-745 is a potent and selective inhibitor of p38A with IC50 of 10 nM; 22-fold greater selectivity versus p38Beta and no inhibition to p38gamma.
PIK-75 is a p110A inhibitor with IC50 of 5.8 nM (200-fold more potently than p110Beta); isoform-specific mutants at Ser773; and also potently inhibits DNA-PK with IC50 of 2 nM.
Alfacalcidol is a non-selective VDR activator medication.
Nelarabine is a purine nucleoside analog and DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 from 0.067-2.15 muM in tumor cells.

VX-222 (VCH-222) is a novel; potent and selective inhibitor of HCV polymerase with IC50 of 0.94-1.2 muM; 15.3-fold less effective for mutant M423T; and 108-fold less effective for mutant I482L. Phase 2.
TAK-632 is a potent pan-Raf inhibitor with IC50 of 8.3 nM and 1.4 nM for B-Raf(wt) and C-Raf; respectively; showing less or no inhibition against other tested kinases.

TG003 is a potent and ATP-competitive Cdc2-like kinase (Clk) inhibitor with IC50 of 20 nM; 200 nM; and 15 nM for Clk1; Clk2; and Clk4; respectively. No inhibitory effect on Clk3; SRPK1; SRPK2; or PKC.
Axitinib is a multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1; VEGFR2; VEGFR3; PDGFRBeta and c-Kit with IC50 of 0.1 nM; 0.2 nM; 0.1-0.3 nM; 1.6 nM and 1.7 nM; respectively.
A cardioprotective agent
Bosutinib (SKI-606) is a novel; dual Src/Abl inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM and 1 nM; respectively.
Topotecan (NSC 609699) is a topoisomerase I inhibitor for MCF-7 Luc cells and DU-145 Luc cells with IC50 of 13 nM and 2 nM; respectively.
Gefitinib (ZD-1839) is an EGFR inhibitor for Tyr1173; Tyr992; Tyr1173 and Tyr992 in the NR6wtEGFR and NR6W cells with IC50 of 37 nM; 37nM; 26 nM and 57 nM; respectively.
Leflunomide is an immunosuppressant agent. Its active metabolite is Teriflunomide.
PD0325901 (PD325901) is selective and non ATP-competitive MEK inhibitor with IC50 of 0.33 nM; roughly 500-fold more potent than CI-1040 on phosphorylation of ERK1 and ERK2. Phase 1/2.
Posaconazole is a sterol C14ɑ demethylase inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.25 nM.
Trichostatin A (TSA) is an HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of ~1.8 nM – HDAC8 is the only known member of the HDAC-family that is not affected by TSA. Phase 3.
Vemurafenib (PLX4032; RG7204) is a novel and potent inhibitor of B-RafV600E with IC50 of 31 nM.
AC480 (BMS-599626) is a selective and efficacious inhibitor of HER1 and HER2 with IC50 of 20 nM and 30 nM; ~8-fold less potent to HER4; >100-fold to VEGFR2; c-Kit; Lck; MET etc. Phase 1.

Quercetin; a polyphenolic flavonoid found in a wide variety of plant-based foods; such as apples; onions; berries; and red wine; is utilized in many different cultures for their nervous system and anticancer effects.
Dimethyl fumarate is a promising novel oral therapeutic option shown to reduce disease activity and progression in patients with relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis.
Silibinin; the main flavonoid extracted from the milk thistle Silybum marianum; displays hepatoprotective properties in acute and chronic liver injury.
Gliclazide (Diamicron) is a whole-cell beta-cell ATP-sensitive potassium currents blocker with an IC50 of 184 +/- 30 nM.
Taxifolin is a flavonoid in many plants such as Taxus chinensis; Siberian larch; Cedrus deodara and so on.
Lonidamine is an orally administered small molecule hexokinase inactivator with an IC50 of 0.85 mM.

Ribitol is a crystalline pentose alcohol and is formed by the reduction of ribose which is occurs naturally in the plant Adonis vernalis.
Alogliptin is a potent; selective inhibitor of DPP-4 with IC50 of <10 nM; exhibits greater than 10;000-fold selectivity over DPP-8 and DPP-9. Phase 4.
PP-121 is a multi-targeted inhibitor of PDGFR; Hck; mTOR; VEGFR2; Src and Abl with IC50 of 2 nM; 8 nM; 10 nM; 12 nM; 14 nM and 18 nM; also inhibits DNA-PK with IC50 of 60 nM.
4-Aminohippuric acid is a typical substrate of organic anion transport systems.
GW3965 is a potent; selective LXRagonist for hLXRA and hLXRBeta with EC50 of 190 and 30 nM; respectively.
SB742457 is a highly selective 5-HT6 receptor antagonist with pKi of 9.63; exhibits >100-fold selectivity over other receptors. Phase 2.
NU7441 is a highly potent and selective DNA-PK inhibitor with IC50 of 14 nM and also inhibits PI3K with IC50 of 5 muM.
Lumiracoxib is a novel; selective COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 and Ki of 0.14 muM and 0.06 muM; exhibits 515-fold selectivity over COX-1. Phase 4.
WAY 100635 is a potent and selective 5-HT1A receptor agonist with pIC50 of 8.87; exhibits >100-fold selectivity against other 5-HT receptor subtypes and major neurotransmitter receptors.
BAY 11-7082 is a NF-kB inhibitor; inhibits TNFA-induced IkBA phosphorylation with IC50 of 10 muM.
Trametinib (GSK1120212) is a highly specific and potent MEK1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.92 nM/1.8 nM; no inhibition of the kinase activities of c-Raf; B-Raf; ERK1/2. Phase 3.
Icotinib is a potent and specific EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM; including the EGFR; EGFR(L858R); EGFR(L861Q); EGFR(T790M) and EGFR(T790M; L858R). Phase 4.
KW-2478 is a nonansamycin HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 3.8 nM. Phase 1/2
Carbazochrome is an antihemorrhagic for use in the treatment of hemorrhoids.
XL335 is a potent; selective FXR agonist with EC50 of 4 nM; highly selective versus other nuclear receptors; such as LXR; PPAR; ER and etc. Phase 1.
Aspirin is a salicylate drug; often used as an analgesic to relieve minor aches and pains; as an antipyretic to reduce fever; and as an anti-inflammatory medication.
YO-01027 (Dibenzazepine; DBZ) is a dipeptidic gamma-secretase inhibitor with IC50 of 2.6 nM and 2.9 nM for APPL and Notch cleavage; respectively.
Piceatannol; a natural stilbene; is a selective Syk inhibitor and ~10-fold selectivity versus Lyn.
JTC-801 is a selective opioid receptor-like1 (ORL1) receptor antagonist with IC50 of 94 nM; weakly inhibits receptors δ; k; and mu.
Fosaprepitant is a water-soluble phosphoryl prodrug for Aprepitant which is a NK1 antagonist.
TG-101348 (SAR302503) is a selective inhibitor of JAK2 with IC50 of 3 nM; 35- and 334-fold more selective for JAK2 versus JAK1 and JAK3. Phase 1/2.
Rupatadine is an inhibitor of PAFR and histamine (H1) receptor with Ki of 550 nM and 102 nM; respectively. Phase 2.
GSK3787 is as a selective and irreversible antagonist of PPARδ with pIC50 of 6.6; with no measurable affinity for hPPARA or hPPARgamma.
Necrostatin-1 is a specific RIP1 inhibitor and inhibits TNF-A-induced necroptosis with EC50 of 490 nM.
AMG 458 is a potent c-Met inhibitor with Ki of 1.2 nM; ~350-fold selectivity for c-Met than VEGFR2 in cells.
Diclofenac diethylamine is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug taken to reduce inflammation and as an analgesic reducing pain in certain conditions.
CUDC-907 is a dual PI3K and HDAC inhibitor for PI3KA and HDAC1/2/3/10 with IC50 of 19 nM and 1.7 nM/5 nM/1.8 nM/2.8 nM; respectively. Phase 1.
Beclomethasone dipropionate  is a potent glucocorticoid steroid used for the treatment of rhinitis and sinusitis.

MK-5108 (VX-689) is a highly selective Aurora A inhibitor with IC50 of 0.064 nM and is 220- and 190-fold more selective for Aurora A than Aurora B/C; while it inhibits TrkA with less than 100-fold selectivity. Phase 1.
Pidotimod is an immunostimulant.
M344 is a potent HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 100 nM and able to induce cell differentiation.
Sulfamerazine is a sulfonamide antibacterial.
INCB28060 is a novel; ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-MET with IC50 of 0.13 nM; inactive against RONBeta; as well as EGFR and HER-3. Phase 1.
Entacapone inhibits catechol-O-methyltransferase (COMT) with IC50 of 151 nM.

AZD4547 is a novel selective FGFR inhibitor targeting FGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 0.2 nM/2.5 nM/1.8 nM; weaker activity against FGFR4; VEGFR2(KDR); and little activity observed against IGFR; CDK2; and p38. Phase 1/2.
Tylosin tartrate is a macrolide antibiotic approved for the control of mycoplasmosis in poultry.

INK 128 is a potent and selective mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM; >200-fold less potent to class I PI3K isoforms; superior in blocking mTORC1/2 and sensitive to pro-invasion genes (vs Rapamycin). Phase 1.
Brinzolamide is a potent carbonic anhydrase II inhibitor with IC50 of 3.19 nM.
NVP-TAE226 is a potent FAK inhibitor with IC50 of 5.5 nM and modestly potent to Pyk2; ~10- to 100-fold less potent against InsR; IGF-1R; ALK; and c-Met.
Ropinirole a selective dopamine D2 receptors inhibitor with IC50 of 29 nM.
Clindamycin inhibits protein synthesis by acting on the 50S ribosomal.
Catharanthine inhibits nicotinic receptor mediated diaphragm contractions with IC50 of 59.6 muM
BRL 54443 is a 5-HT1E and 5-HT1F receptor agonist with pKi of 8.7 and 9.25; respectively; witha weak binding affinity for 5-HT1A; 5-HT1B; 5-HT1D receptors.
Pergolide mesylate is an antiparkinsonian agent which functions as a dopaminergic agonist.
IEM 1754 dihydrobroMide is a selective AMPA/kainate receptor blockers for GluR1 and GluR3 with IC50 of 6 muM.
Ampiroxicam is a nonselective cyclooxygenase inhibitor uesd as anti-inflammatory drug.
PRT062607 (P505-15) HCl is a novel; highly selective Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM; >80-fold selective for Syk than Fgr; Lyn; FAK; Pyk2 and Zap70.
Scriptaid is an inhibitor of HDAC. It shows a greater effect on acetylated H4 than H3.
Clorsulon is used in the treatment of Fasciola hepatica infections in calves and sheep.
TG100713 is a pan-PI3K inhibitor against PI3Kgamma; PI3Kδ; PI3KA and PI3KBeta with IC50 of 50 nM; 24 nM; 165 nM and 215 nM; respectively.
Omecamtivmecarbil (CK-1827452) is a specific cardiac myosinactivator and a clinical drug for left ventricular systolic heart failure. Phase 2.
Acesulfame potassium is a non-nutritive sweetener.
URB597 is a potent; orally bioavailable FAAH inhibitor with IC50 of 4.6 nM; with no activity on other cannabinoid-related targets.
Tyrphostin 9 is firstly designed as an EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 460 muM; but is also found to be more potent to PDGFR with IC50 of 0.5 muM.
SNX-2112 selectively binds to the ATP pocket of HSP90A and HSP90Beta with Ka of 30 nM and 30 nM; uniformly more potent than 17-AAG.

PF-477736 is a selective; potent and ATP-competitive Chk1 inhibitor with Ki of 0.49 nM and also inhibits VEGFR2; Aurora-A; FGFR3; Flt3; Fms (CSF1R); Ret and Yes. It shows ~100-fold selectivity for Chk1 than Chk2. Phase 1.

Clinofibrate inhibits hydroxymethylglutaryl coenzyme A reductase (HMGCR) with IC50 of 0.47 mM; is a lipid-lowering agent used for controlling high cholesterol and triacylglyceride levels in the blood.

Dapivirine is a non-nucleoside inhibitor for HIV reverse transcriptase with IC50 of 24 nM; inhibits a broad panel of HIV-1 isolates from different classes; inclucing a wide range of NNRTI-resistant isolates. Phase 3.
A 922500 is an inhibitor for human and mouse DGAT-1 with IC50 of 7 nM and 24 nM; respectively; good selectivity over related acyltransferases; hERG; and a panel of anti-targets.
Salubrinal is a selective inhibitor of eIF2A dephosphorylation and inhibits ER stress-mediated apoptosis with EC50 of ~15 muM.
NVP-BSK805 is a potent and selective ATP-competitive JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.5 nM;>20-fold selectivity towards JAK1; JAK3 and TYK2.
Clevudine is an antiviral drug for the treatment of hepatitis B.

GDC-0980 (RG7422) is a potent; class I PI3K inhibitor for PI3KA/Beta/δ/gamma with IC50 of 5 nM/27 nM/7 nM/14 nM; respectively. Also a mTOR inhibitor with Ki of 17 nM; and highly selective versus others PIKK family kinases. Phase 2.
Niflumic acid is an inhibitor of cyclooxygenase-2 used for joint and muscular pain.
Geldanamycin is a natural existing HSP90 inhibitor with Kd of 1.2 muM; specifically disrupts glucocorticoid receptor (GR)/HSP association.
Linagliptin is a highly potent; selective DPP-4 inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM.
PH-797804 is a novel pyridinone inhibitor of p38A with IC50 of 26 nM; 4-fold more selective versus p38Beta and does not inhibit JNK2. Phase 2.
Purmorphamine; which directly binds and activates Smoothened; blocks BODIPY-cyclopamine binding to Smo with IC50 of ~ 1.5 muM and also is an inducer of osteoblast differentiation with EC50 of 1 muM.
PAC-1 is a potent procaspase-3 activator with EC50 of 0.22 muM and the first small molecule known to directly activate procaspase-3 to caspase-3.
Azelnidipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker.
Tariquidar (XR9576) is a potent and selective noncompetitive inhibitor of P-glycoprotein with Kd of 5.1 nM; reverses drug resistance in MDR cell Lines. Phase 3.
UPF 1069 is a selective PARP2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.3 muM. It is ~27-fold selective against PARP1.

Anacetrapib (MK0859) is a potent; selective; reversible rhCETP and mutant CETP(C13S) inhibitor with IC50 of 7.9 nM and 11.8 nM; increases HDL-C and decreases LDL-C; does not increase aldosterone or blood pressure. Phase 3.

AmbroxolHCl is a potent inhibitor of the neuronal Na+ channels; inhibits TTX-resistant Na+ currents with IC50 of 35.2 muM and 22.5 muM for tonic and phasic block; inhibits TTX-sensitive Na+ currents with IC50 of 100 muM. Phase 3.
Canagliflozin is a highly potent and selective SGLT2 inhibitor for hSGLT2 with IC50 of 2.2 nM; exhibits 413-fold selectivity over hSGLT1.
Atovaquone is a medication used to treat or prevent for pneumocystis pneumonia; toxoplasmosis; malaria; and babesia.
Dalcetrapib (JTT-705) is a rhCETP inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 muM that increases the plasma HDL cholesterol. Phase 3.
Pyridoxine HCl is a form of vitamin B6.
I-BET151 (GSK1210151A) is a novel selective BET inhibitor for BRD2; BRD3 and BRD4 with IC50 of 0.5 muM; 0.25 muM; and 0.79 muM; respectively.
Sulfamethazine is a sulfonamide antibacterial.
Tofacitinib is a novel inhibitor of JAK3 with IC50 of 1 nM; 20- to 100-fold less potent against JAK2 and JAK1.
Estradiol is a synthetic ester used to treat menopausal symptoms and hormone deficiencies.
Galeterone is a selective CYP17 inhibitor and androgen receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 300 nM and 384 nM; respectively; and is a potent inhibitor of human prostate tumor growth. Phase 2.
Benztropine is a dopamine transporter (DAT) inhibitor with IC50 of 118 nM.
AT101; the R-(-) enantiomer of Gossypol acetic acid; binds with Bcl-2; Bcl-xL and Mcl-1 with Ki of 0.32 muM; 0.48 muM and 0.18 muM; does not inhibit BIR3 domain and BID. Phase 1/2.
Carbenicillin is a semi-synthetic penicillin antibiotic which interferes with cell wall synthesis of gram-negative bacteria while displaying low toxicity.
RG108 is an inhibitor of DNA methyltransferase with IC50 of 115 nM; does not cause trapping of covalent enzymes.
N6-methyl adenosine (N6-methyl ATP) is a base modified analog of adenosine and is found as a minor nucleoside in natural RNAs.
Epiandrosterone is a steroid hormone with weak androgenic activity; is a natural metabolite of DHEA.
Meptazinol is a unique centrally active opioid analgesic; which inhibits [3H]dihydromorphine binding with IC50 of 58 nM.

Carfilzomib (PR-171) is an irreversible proteasome inhibitor with IC50 of <5 nM; displayed preferential in vitro inhibitory potency against the ChT-L activity in the Beta5 subunit; but little or no effect on the PGPH and T-L activities.
Sitagliptin phosphate is a potent inhibitor of DPP-IV with IC50 of 19 nM in Caco-2 cell extracts.
CTEP is a novel; long-acting; orally bioavailable allosteric antagonist of mGlu5 receptor with IC50 of 2.2 nM; shows >1000-fold selectivity over other mGlu receptors.
Desloratadine is a potent antagonist for  human histamine H1 receptor with IC50 of 51 nM.
Apremilast (CC-10004) is a potent and orally active PDE4 and TNF-A inhibitor with IC50 of 74 nM and 77 nM; respectively.
BMS-345541 is a highly selective inhibitor of the catalytic subunits of IKK-2 and IKK-1 with IC50 of 0.3 muM and 4 muM; respectively.
Arecoline is a muscarinic acetylcholine receptor agonist.
T0070907 is a potent and selective PPARgamma inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM; with a >800-fold selectivity over PPARA and PPARδ.
OSI-027 is a selective and potent dual inhibitor of mTORC1 and mTORC2 with IC50 of 22 nM and 65 nM; and more than 100-fold selectivity observed for mTOR than PI3KA; PI3KBeta; PI3Kgamma or DNA-PK.
A-205804 is a potent and selective inhibitor of E-selectin and ICAM-1 expression with IC50 of 20 nM and 25 nM respectively.
BMS-378806 selectively inhibits the binding of HIV-1 gp120 to the CD4receptor with EC50 of 0.85-26.5 nM in virus.
ZM 323881 is a potent and selective VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of <2 nM; almost no activity on VEGFR1; PDGFRBeta; FGFR1; EGFR and ErbB2.
PF-04929113 (SNX-5422) is a potent and selective HSP90 inhibitor with Kd of 41 nM and induces Her-2 degradation with IC50 of 37 nM. Phase 1/2.
JNJ-7777120 is the first potent and selective non-imidazole histamine H4 receptor antagonist with Ki of 4.5 nM; exhibits >1000-fold selectivity over the other histamin receptors.
Ciprofibrate is a peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor agonist.
GW9662 is a selective PPAR antagonist for PPARgamma with IC50 of 3.3 nM; with at least 100 to 1000-fold functional selectivity in cells with PPARgammaversus PPARA and PPARδ.
BRL-15572 is a 5-HT1D receptor antagonist with pKi of 7.9; also shows a considerable affinity at 5-HT1A and 5-HT2B receptors; exhibiting 60-fold selectivity over 5-HT1B receptor.
CHIR-99021 HCl (CT99021) is hydrochloride of CHIR-99021; which is a GSK-3A/Beta inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM/6.7 nM; ability to distinguish between GSK-3 and its closest homologs Cdc2 and ERK2.
R547 is a potent ATP-competitive inhibitor of CDK1/2/4 with Ki of 2 nM/3 nM/1 nM. It is less potent to CDK7 and GSK3A/Beta; while inactive to other kinases.
Rivaroxaban is a direct inhibitor of Factor Xa with Ki and IC50 of 0.4 nM and  0.7 nM; respectively.
A-769662 is a potent; reversible AMPK activator with EC50 of 0.8 muM; little effect on GPPase/FBPase activity.
Ciclopirox ethanolamine (Ciclopirox olamine; HOE 296) is a broad-spectrum antifungal agent working as an iron chelator.
LY411575 is a potent gamma-secretase inhibitor with IC50 of 0.078 nM/0.082 nM (membrane/cell-based); also inhibits Notch clevage with withIC50 of 0.39 nM.
Bindarit exhibits selective inhibition against monocyte chemotactic proteins MCP-1/CCL2; MCP-3/CCL7 and MCP-2/CCL8.

PF-299804 is a potent; irreversible pan-ErbB inhibitor; mostly to EGFR with IC50 of 6 nM; effective against NSCLCs with EGFR or ERBB2 mutations (resistant to gefitinib) as well as those harboring the EGFR T790M mutation. Phase 2.
Rofecoxib is a COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 18 nM.
GSK1070916 is a reversible and ATP-competitive inhibitor of Aurora B/C with IC50 of 3.5 nM/6.5 nM. It displays >100-fold selectivity against the closely related Aurora A-TPX2 complex. Phase 1.
Alverine citrate is a drug used for functional gastrointestinal disorders.
WY 14643 (Pirinixic Acid) is a potent peroxisome proliferator and activator of PPARA with EC50 of 1.5 muM.
GDC-0349 is a potent and selective ATP-competitive inhibitor of mTOR with Ki of 3.8 nM; 790-fold inhibitory effect against PI3KA and other 266 kinases. Phase 1.
NVP-BGT226 is a novel class I PI3K/mTOR inhibitor for PI3KA/Beta/gamma with IC50 of 4 nM/63 nM/38 nM. Phase 1/2.
Naloxone HCl is an opioid inverse agonist drug used to counter the effects of opiate overdose.
NVP-BVU972 is a selective and potent Met inhibitor with IC50 of 14 nM.
Etravirine (TMC125) is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI) used for the treatment of HIV.

SB705498 is a TRPV1 antagonist for hTRPV1; antagonizes capsaicin; acid; and heat activation of TRPV1 with IC50 of 3 nM; 0.1 nM and 6 nM; shows a degree of voltage dependence; exhibits >100-fold selectivity for TRPV1 over TRPM8. Phase 2.
Vitamin C is a water-soluble vitamin indicated for the prevention and treatment of scurvy.
RITA (NSC 652287) induces both DNA-protein and DNA-DNA cross-links with no detectable DNA single-strand breaks; and also inhibits MDM2-p53 interaction by targeting p53.
Sodium salicylate is used in medicine as an analgesic and antipyretic.
Istradefylline is a selective adenosine A2A receptor (A2AR) antagonist with Ki of 2.2 nM.
Articaine is a dental local anesthetic which contains an additional ester group that is metabolized by estearases in blood and tissue.
Sirtinol is a specific SIRT1 and SIRT2 inhibitor with IC50 of 131 muM and 38 muM; respectively.
Altrenogest is a progestogen structurally related to veterinary steroid trenbolone.
Ciproxifan is a highly potent and selective histamin H3-receptor antagonist with IC50 of 9.2 nM; with low apparent affinity at other receptor subtypes.
Eletriptan is a selective 5-HT1B and 5-HT1D receptor agonist with Ki of 0.92 nM and 3.14 nM; respectively.
OC000459 is a potent and selective D prostanoid receptor 2 (DP2) antagonist with IC50 of 13 nM.
Ticarcillin is a semisynthetic antibiotic with a broad spectrum of bactericidal activity against many gram-positive and gram-negative aerobic and anaerobic bacteria.
ARN-509 is a selective and competitive androgen receptor inhibitor with IC50 of 16 nM; useful for prostate cancer treatment. Phase 2.
Fexofenadine inhibits histamine H1 receptor with IC50 of 246 nM.
BML-190 is a selective cannabinoid CB2 receptor inverse agonist with Ki of 435 nM; with 50-fold selectivity over CB1 receptor.

Lithocholic acid is a toxic secondary bile acid; causes intrahepatic cholestasis; has tumor-promoting activity; its toxic effect can be protected after it activates the vitamin D receptor; PXR and FXR.
VU 0364770 is a positive allosteric modulator(PAM) of mGlu4 with EC50 of 1.1 muM; exhibits insignificant activity at 68 other receptors; including other mGlu subtypes.
Hyoscyamine is an AChR inhibitor with IC50 of 7.5 nM.
VU 0364439 is a mGlu4 positive allosteric modulator (PAM); with EC50 of 19.8 nM.

Dynasore is a cell-permeable; reversible non-competitive dynamin inhibitor of GTPase activity of dynamin 1/2; with IC50 of 15 muM; also inhibits the mitochondrial dynamin Drp1; with no effect against other small GTPase.
Noradrenaline bitartrate monohydrate is a direct alpha-adrenergic receptors stimulator.
GW5074 is a potent and selective c-Raf inhibitor with IC50 of 9 nM; no effect on the activities of JNK1/2/3; MEK1; MKK6/7; CDK1/2; c-Src; p38 MAP; VEGFR2 or c-Fms is noted.
Fostamatinib (R788); a prodrug of the active metabolite R406; is a Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 41 nM; strongly inhibits Syk but not Lyn; 5-fold less potent to Flt3. Phase 2.
PJ-34 is a PARP inhibitor with EC50 of 20 nM and is equally potent to PARP1/2.
NPS 2143 is a novel potent and selective antagonist of Ca(2+) receptor with IC50 of 43 nM.
ZM 306416 is a VEGFR (Flt and KDR) inhibitor for VEGFR1 with IC50 of 0.33 muM; but also found to inhibit EGFR with IC50 of <10 nM.
GSK2126458 is a highly selective and potent inhibitor of p110A/Beta/δ/gamma; mTORC1/2 with Ki of 0.019 nM/0.13 nM/0.024 nM/0.06 nM and 0.18 nM/0.3 nM; respectively. Phase 1.

Ki16198 is the methyl ester of Ki16425; which is a LPA antagonist and inhibits LPA1- and LPA3-induced inositol phosphate production with Ki of 0.34 muM and 0.93 muM; respectively; shows weaker inhibition for LPA2; no activity at LPA4; LPA5; LPA6.
PF-3845 is a potent; selective and irreversible FAAH inhibitor with Ki of 230 nM; showing negligible activity against FAAH2.
ML-161 is an allosteric inhibitor of PAR1 with IC50 of 0.26 muM.

Flavopiridol competes with ATP to inhibit CDKs including CDK1; CDK2; CDK4 and CDK6 with IC50 of ~ 40 nM. It is 7.5-fold more selective for CDK1/2/4/6 than CDK7. Flavopiridol is initially found to inhibit EGFR and PKA. Phase 1/2.
Evacetrapib (LY2484595) is a potent and selective inhibitor of CETP with IC50 of 5.5 nM; elevates HDL cholesterol without increases in aldosterone or blood pressure. Phase 3.

WAY-600 is a potent; ATP-competitive and selective inhibitor of mTOR with IC50 of 9 nM; blocks mTORC1/P-S6K(T389) and mTORC2/P-AKT(S473) but not P-AKT(T308); selective for mTOR than PI3KA (>100-fold) and PI3Kgamma (>500-fold).
Paroxetine is an antidepressant drug of the SSRI type.
RS-127445 is a selective 5-HT2B receptor antagonist with pKi of 9.5 and pIC50 of 10.4; exhibits >1000-fold selectivity against other 5-HT receptors.
Rimonabant is a selective antagonist of CB1 with IC50 of 13.6 nM and EC50 of 17.3 nM in hCB1 transfected HEK 293 membrane.
CP-91149 is a selective glycogen phosphorylase (GP) inhibitor with IC50 of 0.13 muM in the presence of glucose; 5- to 10-fold less potent in the absence of glucose.
Vildagliptin (LAF-237) inhibits DPP−4 with IC50 of 2.3 nM.
AG-1478 (Tyrphostin AG-1478) is a selective EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM; almost no activity on HER2-Neu; PDGFR; Trk; Bcr-Abl and InsR.
Cinepazide maleate is a maleate salt form of cinepazide which is a vasodilator.

PHA-767491 is a potent ATP-competitive dual Cdc7/CDK9 inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM and 34 nM; respectively.It displays ~20-fold selectivity against CDK1/2 and GSK3-Beta; 50-fold selectivity against MK2 and CDK5; 100-fold selectivity against PLK1 and CHK2.
Azilsartan Medoxomil is a potent angiotensin II type 1 (AT1) receptor antagonist; inhibits the RAAS; with an IC50 of 2.6 nM; exhibits >10;000-fold selectivity over AT2. Phase 3.
NSC 23766 is an inhibitor of Rac GTPase targeting Rac activation by guanine nucleotide exchange factors (GEFs) with IC50 of ~50 muM; does not inhibit the closely related  targets; Cdc42 or RhoA.
GW2580 is a selective CSF-1R inhibitor for c-FMS with IC50 of 30 nM; 150- to 500-fold selective compared to b-Raf; CDK4; c-KIT; c-SRC; EGFR; ERBB2/4; ERK2; FLT-3; GSK3; ITK; JAK2 etc.
GW788388 is a potent and selective inhibitor of ALK5 with IC50 of 18 nM; also inhibits TGF-Beta type II receptor and activin type II receptor activities; but does not inhibit BMP type II receptor.
Piracetam is a cyclic derivative of the neurotransmitter gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA); used in treatment of a wide range of cognitive disorders.
CH5424802 is a potent ALK inhibitor with IC50 of 1.9 nM; sensitive to L1196M mutation and higher selectivity for ALK than PF-02341066; NVP-TAE684 and PHA-E429. Phase 1/2.
Ulipristal is a selective SPRM for emergency contraception after an unprotected intercourse or contraceptive failure.

MK-2461 is a potent; multi-targeted inhibitor for c-Met(WT/mutants) with IC50 of 0.4-2.5 nM; less potent to Ron; Flt1; 8- to 30-fold greater selectivity of c-Met targets versus FGFR1; FGFR2; FGFR3;PDGFRBeta; KDR; Flt3; Flt4; TrkA; and TrkB. Phase 1/2.
Sulfathiazole is an organosulfur compound that has been used as a short-acting sulfa drug.
GW4064 is an agonist of farnesoid X receptor (FXR) with EC50 of 65 nM.
Methylthiouracil is an antithyroid preparation.
Sotrastaurin is a potent and selective pan-PKC inhibitor; mostly for PKCθ with Ki of 0.22 nM; inactive to PKCζ. Phase 1/2.
Gliquidone is an ATP-sensitive K+ channel antagonist with IC50 of 27.2 nM.
LY364947 is a potent ATP-competitive inhibitor of TGFBetaR-I with IC50 of 59 nM; shows 7-fold selectivity over TGFBetaR-II.
Ampicillin is a beta-lactam antibiotic that is part of the aminopenicillin family.
BYL719 is a potent and selective PI3KA inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM; and minimal effect on PI3KBeta/gamma/δ. Phase 1/2.
Flumequine is a synthetic chemotherapeutic antibiotic; inhibiting topoisomerase II with IC50 of 15 muM.
Tideglusib is an irreversible; non ATP-competitive GSK-3Beta inhibitor with IC50 of 60 nM; fails to inhibit kinases with a Cys homologous to Cys-199 located in the active site. Phase 1/2.
Azlocillin is an acylampicillin with a broad spectrum against bacteria.
SAR131675 is a VEGFR3 inhibitor with IC50/Ki of 23 nM/12 nM; about 50- and 10-fold more selective for VEGFR3 than VEGFR1/2; little activity against Akt1; CDKs; PLK1; EGFR; IGF-1R; c-Met; Flt2 etc.
Amidopyrine is white crystalline substance used as an analgesic and antipyretic.
MRS2578 is a potent P2Y6 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 37 nM; exhibits insignificant activity at P2Y1; P2Y2; P2Y4;and P2Y11 receptors.
Ethambutol is a bacteriostatic antimycobacterial agent; which obstructs the formation of cell wall by inhibiting arabinosyl transferases.
ML130 is a potent and selective inhibitor of NOD1 with IC50 of 0.56 muM; inhibits NF-kB activation; exhibits 36-fold selectivity over NOD2.
Cyclamic acid in the form of its sodium or calcium salt is one of the most widely used artificial sweeteners.
Butein; a plant polyphenol isolated from Rhus verniciflua; is able to inhibit the activation of protein tyrosine kinase; NF-kB and STAT3; also inhibits EGFR
ABT-199 (GDC-0199) is a Bcl-2-selective inhibitor with Ki of <0.01 nM; >4800-fold more selective versus Bcl-xL and Bcl-w; and no activity to Mcl-1. Phase 2.
TAK-733 is a potent and selective MEK allosteric site inhibitor for MEK1 with IC50 of 3.2 nM; inactive to Abl1; AKT3; c-RAF; CamK1; CDK2; c-Met; etc. Phase 1.
Camostat is a trypsin-like protease inhibitor; inhibits airway epithelial sodium channel (ENaC) function with IC50 of 50 nM; less potent to trpsin; prostasin and matriptase.
LY2603618 is a selective Chk1 inhibitor with potential anti-tumor activity.

PF-562271 is a potent; ATP-competitive; reversible inhibitor of FAK with IC50 of 1.5 nM; ~10-fold less potent for Pyk2 than FAK and >100-fold selectivity against other protein kinases; except for some CDKs.
